node.text: Such a rad time with an awesome group of peoples. The @GridExperience definitely sets the bar (and sets it pretty high) for me when it comes to indoor karting. Combine that with a this crew of friends and fam: Jeremy McGrath, Sage Kotsenburg, Zak Hale, Davey Coombs (founder of Racer X), Zac Mertens (of Hoonigan Racing), etc. - plus Jett and Hunter Lawrence were two of the top three fastest of the night (same positions as they finished in the 250 Main of the Supercross race this past weekend!). Jeremy’s daughter (Rhowan) and my daughter (Lia) both had two of the top lap five times also (yep, we’re proud Dads!). Good times!

node.title: Rad time karting at The Grid Experience with friends and fam.

node.text: This weekend will be my first competitive drive in a Subaru since 2009. With only one proper day of testing before @AlexGelsomino and I show up this weekend to the @OlympusRally (3rd round of the @ARA_Rally Championship) it will be interesting to see how quickly I can get fully comfortable in it and run at full tilt. But so far, the car looks (livery by @ItsALiving) and feels (built and prepped by Vermont SportsCar) great! Check out this week's episode on my YouTube channel (link in bio) for the livery reveal, and to hear about all our plans for a wild year! #gravelslayingaction

node.text: Here’s another AINT CARE moment from the vault: @AlexGelsomino and I lost our front right side wheel midway through Stage 3 (of Oregon Trail Rally in 2013) due to a freak mechanical failure. We kept the hammer down and finished that stage, and then continued on to run another full stage on just 3 wheels, rather than settling for a DNF. We finished the race 2nd overall - all because we were able to drive through this #AINTCARE situation!

node.title: JUST AIN’T CARE from Oregon Trail Rally 2013

node.text: AIN’T CARE, rally cross example: after qualifying first, winning each of the heats, and leading the first 5 laps of the Final in the 2012 GRC race in Las Vegas, the ECU/control panel in my race car caught fire. I continued the race for as long as I could, but the fumes from the fire were starting to burn my lungs. I led and raced for as long as I could but eventually had to stop. I truly tried to AIN’T CARE as long as I could, but wasn’t willing to die for the win. 🤷‍♂️ #AINTCARE #pressonregardless

node.title: AIN’T CARE - GRC Las Vegas - FIRE

node.text: Lots of rain prior to The Rally in the 100 Acre Wood this year made for some very wet and rough stretches of the race stages. Click the link to see the full on-board video from the entire 10.84 mile stage. #100AW

node.text: Enjoy this dual-onboard video from Stage 7 (Asbridge Hollow) from this weekend’s Rally In The 100 Acre Wood. @AlexGelsomino and I were fastest on this stage to start off Saturday morning. This is a great example of just how fast and technical the stages are around Salem and how competitive the weekend was (the top four cars all finished this 4.3 mile long stage within 5 seconds of each other). #100AW

node.text: Not sure which is a tighter fit: the turbocharged Hayabusa engine in Cole Powelson’s @sierracars <or> Hoonigan’s @brianscotto (aka El Gigante) in the driver's seat of that Corvette!! This turned out to be a great race, with a bit of a plot twist towards the end. Comment below who you think won, then click the link to watch the race in @thehoonigans episodic race series: This Vs. That. #Hoonigan #thisvsthat

I have had an issue in my left shoulder for many years now (moto crashes have taken their toll!), but with the right training, equipment, and great products like the @cbdmd.usa Freeze, I have been able to heal and improve the situation. Big thanks to Ted Bezmer (trainer) his invention (the Axio 360 LT), and cbdMD for all the help! #motoinjuriessuck #cbdMD #Axio360LT

node.text: I love seeing Porsches shredding in the dirt. Although this one is much more modern than the Tuthill Porsche I will be racing in the East African Safari Classic Rally, I still really want to try it out! TJ Russel (@russellbuiltfabrication ) built it for racing races such as the Baja 1000, but I think it might do quite good on a rally stage! Hit up TJ and tell him to let me test it out!! (thanks in advance for the help!) #highendgravelslayer #Baja911

node.text: “Ain’t Care” apparently is a hereditary thing! No parent likes to see their kid (in this case, my daughter Lia) get flipped over during a race… BUT seeing your kid brush themselves off, get back out on course, and beat the kid who flipped her over is a level of pride that is hard to put into words. I love this kid’s determination! 📸: @driveby.shootings  #aintcare #kartingdadlife

First thought: rip some moto laps in the dark! Good idea or nah?? #RigidIndustries
